<BaseLayout title="About | Rishika Miranda" description="The design philosophy and journey of Rishika Miranda, founder of Kyrah Design Studio.">
  <article class="space-y-12">
    
    <div>
      <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold tracking-tight text-stone-900 sm:text-4xl mb-2">About</h1>
      <p class="text-sm font-medium text-stone-500 tracking-wide uppercase">Architect, Interior Designer & Studio Founder</p>
    </div>

    <div class="text-stone-600 leading-relaxed space-y-6 text-base sm:text-[17px]">
      <p>
        I’m the founder of <a href="https://kyrah.in" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="text-stone-900 font-medium underline decoration-stone-300 underline-offset-4 hover:text-stone-600 transition">Kyrah Design Studio</a>, a Bangalore-based interior design practice focused on creating thoughtfully crafted residential spaces. 
      </p>
      
      <p>
        Over the past five years, I’ve had the opportunity to build Kyrah from the ground up—shaping not just the physical homes we design, but also the way we approach collaboration, deep material craftsmanship, and site execution.
      </p>

      <p>
        My work sits squarely at the intersection of design vision and real-world implementation. While great spaces often begin as ethereal ideas and sketches, bringing them to life requires meticulous coordination with clients, master craftsmen, contractors, and specialized vendors. 
      </p>

      <p>
        Being deeply involved on-site has fundamentally shaped how I think about design—as something that must be both visually inspiring and inherently buildable.
      </p>

      <p>
        At Kyrah, we work closely with homeowners to create spaces that feel personal, layered, and timeless. Many of our projects draw intentionally from traditional Indian craftsmanship and material richness while being sensitively adapted for contemporary living.
      </p>

      <p>
        As a studio founder, I’m equally passionate about building a strong, curious team culture where open collaboration, shared curiosity, and active problem-solving are part of the everyday creative process. Five years into this journey, what continues to excite me most is the endless opportunity to keep learning—from projects, from people on site, and from the evolving world of design.
      </p>
    </div>

